The global automotive foam market is expected to witness significant growth by 2029, driven by various factors such as increasing demand for lightweight materials in the automotive industry, rising focus on energy efficiency, and advancements in foam technologies. The market is segmented based on type, application, and end-use. Polyurethane foam, polyolefin foam, polyvinyl chloride (PVC) foam, phenolic foam, melamine foam, and others are the key types of foam utilized in the automotive sector. These foams find applications in seating, door panels, bumper systems, and other automotive components. The OEM segment dominates the end-use category, owing to the rising production of vehicles globally.

